node.text:
What a fun chat on identity. Thank you to everyone who joined me live here on Instagram. 

Here’s the structure of the chat: 

• the question I’m curious about answering
• an explanation of lower and higher vibrations
• an explanation of genuine self-compassion
• step one
• step two
• step three
• summary

node.text:
The first step towards letting go is giving up the obsessive chase to be liked, agreed with, accepted, validated. It's fantastic when we find agreement and when we are validated, that is good for everyone. However, we have to make sure we are not self-abandoning for "approval".

That in itself gives you a great deal of freedom and reign to live your most authentic self.

Comment below and let me know what your thoughts are! 

On August 13th, I'm doing an immersive deep dive into the subject of letting go. I'll teach you how to let go and how to enable the peace of mind you deserve. Go to the link in my bio and reserve your spot in "The Art Of Letting Go Workshop."

node.title: Letting Go: Let Go Of Other People's Approval

node.text:
Speak good energy and life into yourself every single day. Always use self-compasdion when you talk about your journey. As a consequence of self-compassion, your vibration will change. As a consequence of a raised vibration, you'll find it easier to set boundaries.

I'm going live tomorrow on Instagram. Send me your questions or topics you’d like me to cover via direct message. Turn on my post notifications, so you don't miss when I go live!

node.title: How Do I Speak Up For Myself

node.text:
This clip is from a mini-episode of the Free Your Energy podcast. Grab it on Spotify or iTunes.

If you enjoy long-form podcasts, you'll love hearing me jam with world-class teachers, storytellers, and people with immense passion.

During the week, I do mini-episodes on different topics that inspire me!  If you NEED more words on overthinking, I have a mini-course called “How To Stop Overthinking.” You can grab that from Sylvestermcnutt.net/courses

I hope you get into the activity, action, and into the mud! It's the only way to create what you're envisioning!

node.text:
Focusing on what is outside of you is a path to stress, anxiety, confusion, and who knows what else.

node.text:
What a fun chat on identity. Thank you to everyone who joined me live here on Instagram. 

Here’s the structure of the chat: 

• the question I’m curious about answering
• an explanation of lower and higher vibrations
• an explanation of genuine self-compassion
• step one
• step two
• step three
• summary

node.text:
Drop a 💛 To Claim this!⁠
⁠
Workshop Alert: I am so excited to tell you about my new workshop, The Art Of Letting Go. On August 13th, I will be teaching you a framework on "HOW to let go."⁠
⁠
In this 1 hour workshop, you will leave with concrete strategies that work, you'll be a step closer to letting go, and you will have a solid plan to manage when strong emotions come up. I'll open with a deep monologue, and then the rest of the time is Q&A.⁠
⁠
Go reserve your spot today by visiting the link in my bio and register for the "Art Of Letting Go" Workshop.⁠
⁠
FAQ: ⁠
- If I can't make it live, can I watch it on-demand? Yes⁠
- Price? One time payment of USD 97⁠
- How to register? link in bio or iamlettinggo.net

node.text:
Share this to your story if you felt this!

Your belief system is the most important key point indicator in your life. Your behavior, habits, reactions and over reactions come from your belief systems.

As a personal development coach and author, the work is to get people to examine their belief systems (without shame). You cannot use shame to transform. If you’re looking to align your life I invite you to examine your belief systems as an objective observer, and to then deeply examine the consequences of your beliefs.

—

I’m so excited for the Art Of Letting Go workshop on August 13th! We’ll have space to take about shifting/letting go of belief systems. This work has to be done with self-compassion, otherwise, it’ll never work. Join me by going to the link in my bio and securing your spot. Or, you can register directly on the site here: Iamlettinggo.net

node.text:
The first step towards letting go is giving up the obsessive chase to be liked, agreed with, accepted, validated. It's fantastic when we find agreement and when we are validated, that is good for everyone. However, we have to make sure we are not self-abandoning for "approval".

That in itself gives you a great deal of freedom and reign to live your most authentic self.

Comment below and let me know what your thoughts are! 

On August 13th, I'm doing an immersive deep dive into the subject of letting go. I'll teach you how to let go and how to enable the peace of mind you deserve. Go to the link in my bio and reserve your spot in "The Art Of Letting Go Workshop."

node.text:
I hope you find comfort in these words today.

I’ve been processing some “life changes” lately, and what I am recognizing is that there’s a duality between pushing and pulling.

A duality between manifesting and allowing. When I was much younger and had unresolved trauma, I wanted to “control” more of my situations. Why? Because control appears to create safety. The allusion to safety helps you move through the world, and of course, nobody wants “more pain” or “discomfort.”

But as I healed and entered more aligned situations, I noticed something. Control has no place in manifesting abundance, in friendships, in partnerships. The need to control goes away the more you heal because you have more trust! 

Once I got through the trauma, I began to see that everything in life is about alignment, collaboration, and creating a safe space to have conversations (this was my recognition but doesn't mean it's true for anyone else).

Energetically, this place has created pure abundance and clarity, and for that, I am grateful. Moving from this energy field has 10x’d my career, my health and my overall mental health. 

Let it flow, friend, let it flow.

I hope you enjoyed this quote from my book, Free Your Energy. It’s closing in on 600 5-star reviews on amazon, which is unheard of for an independent author. If you got value out of the book, please jump on amazon and leave a review for me. It means a lot to me.

Have a great week!

node.text:
Type "YES" Below to claim this energy.⁠
⁠
You are responsible for your energy. As soon as you commit to those "I'm about to get back at them" or "I need to prove them wrong" energy commitments, what is actually happening? All you are doing is making a bond with that energy.⁠
⁠
Is that what you want? ⁠
⁠
What are the consequences of that energy?⁠
⁠
Be clear, is that genuinely what you want?⁠
⁠
Everyone in my close circle hears me say this every day: focus on what you want and Build Your Boundaries around what you don't want. That includes people who have the petty "get back at you" mindset.⁠
⁠
Those are not your people, and that energy is not for you! If you can see this message, I promise you that you have a higher calling and a deeper purpose for your energy.⁠
⁠
The best solution is not to "get even"; the best solution is to use your boundaries and voice and be intentional with putting your energy.⁠
⁠
I hope you have a great week.⁠
⁠
Choose your energy wisely, and everything will align for you properly. Life is energy. If you need help setting boundaries and you want me to teach you HOW step-by-step, go to Buildyourboundaries.net and get in my course. ⁠
⁠
⁠
